      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Dataset copied from the CD obtained from Washington DC 2005

An excel spreadsheet containing Bank Branch address information in DC was received by the Department of Insurance, Securities and Banking (DISB).  The data was cleaned up and imported into MS Access for use with the MAR Batch Geocoder.  13 of 223 records did not match automatically.  Several were simply misspelled or had the wrong quadrant.  Address information was verified using each Branch's official web site.  4 records were not found in the MAR and were submitted to the MAR team.</procdesc>
        <procdate>2007</procdate>
        <proccont>
          <cntinfo>
            <cntorgp>
              <cntorg>Office of the Chief Technology Officer</cntorg>
              <cntper>GIS Data Coordinator</cntper>
            </cntorgp>
            <cntaddr>
              <addrtype>mailing and physical address</addrtype>
              <address>441 4th St NW, Suite 930 South</address>
              <city>Washington</city>
              <state>DC</state>
              <postal>20001</postal>
              <country>USA</country>
            </cntaddr>
            <cntvoice/>
            <cntfax>202-727-5660</cntfax>
            <cntemail>dcgiss@dc.gov</cntemail>
          </cntinfo>
        </proccont>
      </procstep>
      <procstep>
        <procdesc>The Access database was then imported into ArcMap.  An even theme was created to display the X,Y coordinates.  The event theme was then exported into a feature class.  The remaining 4 records that did not have a MAR address point were then manually geocoded to the file.</procdesc>
        <procdate>040407</procdate>
      </procstep>
